{"type_article": "Article", "title": "Hong Kong under Chinese Sovereignty: Social Development and a Land (Re)development Regime", "link": "https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.2747/1539-7216.49.3.341", "author_list": ["Wing-Shing   Tang"], "journal_name": "Eurasian Geography and Economics Volume 49, 2008 - Issue 3", "date": " 15 May 2013", "abstract": "A Hong Kong\u2014based human geographer presents a paper on the city's social development and its domination by land and real estate developers (a state of affairs he terms the \"[re]development regime\"). The author analyzes the route and composition of the participants of an Olympic torch relay in the city, which demonstrates the influence of that regime. Before focusing on the regime's role in impeding alternative options for urban (and distorting societal) development, the paper discusses Hong Kong's social rankings, including a comparison with China and the United States, as well as the increasing social inequality, the rising cost of living (particularly food and energy prices), and the prohibitive cost of apartment rentals. \n, Classification Numbers: H10, L85, O15, R14, R31. 8 figures, 3 tables, 37 references.", "doi": "", "keyword_list": ["Keywords:", "Hong Kong", "China", "Beijing Olympic torch relay", "social development", "rental prices", "real estate", "urban development", "land redevelopment", "cost of living", "corruption", "quality of life", "Index of Economic Freedom", "Human Development Index"], "citation_count": 0, "reference_list": [" Adams, D. and E. M. Hastings,  \"Assessing Institutional Relations in Development Partnerships: The Land Development Corporation and the Hong Kong Government prior to 1997,\"  Urban Studies , 38, 9:1473-1492, 2001a. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Adams, D. and E. M. Hastings,  \"Urban Renewal in Hong Kong: Transition from Development Corporation to Renewal Authority,\"  Land Use Policy , 18, 3:245-258, 2001b. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Allen, J., Lost Geographies of Power.  Oxford, UK: Blackwell, 2003. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Anacker, S.,  \"Geographies of Power in Nazarbayev's Astana,\"  Eurasian Geography and Economics , 45, 7:515-533, 2004. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Chan, E. and G. K. L. Lee,  \"Critical Factors for Improving Social Sustainability of Urban Renewal Projects,\"  Social Indicators Research , 85, 2:243-256, 2008. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD (Census and Statistics Department), Hong Kong Annual Digest of Statistics 2001.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong SAR Government, 2001. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD, 2004/05 Household Expenditure Survey and the Rebasing of the Consumer Price Indices.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong SAR Government, 2006. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD,  \"Government Revenue (General Revenue Account and Funds),\" November 1, 2007a [ http://www.censtatd.gov.hk/showtableexcel2.jsp?tableID=193  \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD, Hong Kong Annual Digest of Statistics 2007.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong SAR Government, 2007b. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD,  \"Statistics on Comprehensive Social Secirity Assistance Scheme 1996-2006,\"  Hong Kong Monthly Digest of Statistics.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong SAR Government, 2007c. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " CSD,  \"The Movement of the Unemployed Rate,\"  Hong Kong Monthly Digest of Statistics.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong SAR Government, 2008. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Economist, The World in 2007.  London, UK: Economist Newspaper Ltd., 2006. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Freedom House, Freedom in the World 2006.  Washington, DC: Freedom House, 2007. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Fung, B. Y., A Century of Hong Kong Real Estate Development.  Hong Kong: Joint Publishing House, 2001 (in Chinese). \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Goodstadt, L. F., Uneasy Partners: The Conflict between Public Interest and Private Profit in Hong Kong.  Hong Kong: Hong Kong University Press, 2005. \u00a0[Google Scholar]", " Heritage Foundation,  \"Index of Economic Freedom,\" 2008 [ http://www.heritage.org/index/countries  \u00a0