{"type_article": "Article", "title": "Comparative analysis of agriculture and rural policies in V\u00e4sterbotten and Hordaland using the POMMARD-model", "link": "https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/16507541.2011.607589", "author_list": ["Sara   Alva-Lizarraga", "Karen   Refsgaard", "Thomas G.   Johnson"], "journal_name": "Acta Agriculturae Scandinavica, Section C \u2014 Food Economics Volume 8, 2011 - Issue 3", "date": " 17 Aug 2011", "abstract": "The Towards a Policy Model of Multifunctional Agriculture and Rural Development project explored the complex interrelationships between policies, the multiple functions of farming, the development of rural regions and the quality of life of their inhabitants. It demonstrated that the same policy interventions in different regions could lead to varying outcomes depending on the local economic, social and environmental contexts.This paper builds on previous work by Johnson et al. and Bryden et al. It further explores these relationships and evaluates the extent to which social, economic and environmental variables are affected by the implementation of policy in different jurisdictions. We compare Hordaland in Norway with V\u00e4sterbotten in Sweden. Results support the conclusions of Bryden et al. and sustain the notion that Hordaland agriculture is more \u2018multifunctional\u2019 than V\u00e4sterbotten and stress the link between rural and agricultural policies, and quality of life in rural regions.", "doi": "https://doi.org/10.1080/16507541.2011.607589", "keyword_list": ["Keywords:", "CAP", "dynamic simulation modelling", "environmental impacts", "quality of life", "multifunctionality", "policy scenario", "rural development", "system dynamics", "territorial development"], "citation_count": 0, "reference_list": ["  \r\nAndersen  ,   C.     and    \r\nEllingsen  ,   W.     2003   Reiselivsn\u00e6ringer og turistkonsum i Hordaland. Samfunns- og n\u00e6ringslivsforskning [The tourism industry and tourism consumption